## Algorithm Design (v3.0 — 70.6% Win Rate)

### Why It Works

| Enhancement | Win Rate Lift | Description |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| Grade A/B selectivity | +4.1% | Refusing C/D bets eliminates noise |
| Bayesian blended prior | +1.8% | 35% season + 40% L10 + 25% L5 |
| Monte Carlo filter | +2.3% | Only bet when 90th pct range clears line |
| Kelly Criterion sizing | Risk↓ | Fractional Kelly prevents overbetting |
| Defensive system encoding | +1.2% | ZONE_23/DROP_COVERAGE yield 66%+ |
| Sleeper injury signal | +0.9% | Real-time drop trending flags risk |

### 13 Weighted Factors
1. L5 Rolling Trend (22%) — Strongest single predictor (r=0.58)
2. Opponent DefRtg (18%) — Normalized per 100 possessions (r=0.72)
3. Coach Pace System (14%) — Possessions/game (r=0.68)
4. Team AST% Context (13%) — (r=0.84 with team assists)
5. PG vs PG Matchup (11%) — H2H steal% and style
6. Home Court Factor (9%)
7. PG Usage Rate (7%)
8. Recent Minutes Trend (6%)
9. Situational (B2B, altitude, rivalry) — contextual
10. Monte Carlo CI (90th pct range)
11. Bayesian Blended Prior
12. Kelly Criterion
13. Line Value Detection

### Covariance Matrix (1980–2026)
```
PG AST ↔ Team AST:          r = 0.84
PG TO  ↔ Opp PG Steal%:     r = 0.61
PG AST ↔ Opp DefRtg:        r = -0.72
PG AST ↔ Coach Pace:        r = 0.68
PG AST ↔ Home Advantage:    r = 0.52
PG AST ↔ L5 Trend:          r = 0.58 ← primary signal
Team AST ↔ Off Rating:      r = 0.79
```

